<title>USA: Comcast approves Scripps unit purchase.</title>
<headline>Comcast approves Scripps unit purchase.</headline>
<dateline>PHILADELPHIA 1996-11-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>Comcast Corp said its shareholders voted to approve the issuance of Comcast class A special common stock for the purchase of E.W. Scripps Co's television operations.</p>
<p>The company said it expects to issue about 93.3 million shares of the stock under the deal.</p>
<p>Scripps holds the right to terminate the deal if Comcast's share price falls below $17.06 during a defined pricing period.</p>
<p>The deal is scheduled to close on November 13, 1996, Comcast said.  </p>
<p>.</p>
